snippet.textDisplay:
This woman is a gift to Pakistan after Reshman & Abida Parveen. It's so heartening to have a similar voice & soulful singer in this generation which I had thought we'll lose after the legends will be gone. QB is a perfect fusion of eastern & western music. She knows modern music, yet is fully capable of handling Sufism. Could one ask for more?

This song is absolute food for soul. The music, especially the drums steal the show. Initially, me & many others, felt that QB didn't sing it to her full vocal potential, later to realize that it's only due to us being tuned to the high notes of every version of this song, since childhood. 

However, if listened to it in dept, we realize how amazingly Coke Studio has revamped it, giving it it's own touch which is taking it to another high altogether & is of its own kind. 

The best way to enjoy a Coke Studio song is to open oneself to its novelties, keeping aside the prejudice of them laying hands on the classics. This song which immediately didn't catch much of my attention is now the most wholesome experience in my playlist. Absolutely therapeutic!!

Way to go Quratulain Baloch! You are a treat to the world along-with the beautiful packaging of Coke Studio Pakistan.
